-From a single ontological commitment---that irreversible actualization events writing permanent vertices into a growing causal graph, filtered by the BDG action, are the primitive physical reality---this paper has established the kernel of Relational Actualism: seven axioms, a sequential growth rule, an acceptance kernel characterized by two Lean-verified identities, and a four-level actualization criterion. From the kernel, the measurement problem is dissolved at the level of the low-density limit; special-relativistic kinematics emerges from the graph bandwidth; and $d=4$ emerges as the unique dimension satisfying all identified viability criteria simultaneously.
-
-The claims in this paper are not uniformly rigorous. Some are Lean-verified theorems (the Kernel--Poisson identity, the integer-core coupling-constant identities, the BDG coefficient uniqueness at the arithmetic layer). Some are Lean-verified conditional on disclosed axioms (the Rindler stationarity theorem used in the Unruh resolution, which depends on \texttt{vacuum\_lorentz\_invariant} as a QFT input---a known open target). Some are computation-verified (the exact $\Delta S^*$ value, the D4U02 selectivity maximum). Others are derivations within the framework whose bridge identifications (the kinematic identifications, the coupling-constant preview, the framework-wide predictions) are sharpened in the companion papers. The epistemic-status table above labels each claim accordingly.
-
-Paper~II develops the particle spectrum and force hierarchy from the BDG topology classes. Paper~III develops gravity, cosmology, and the severance programme. Paper~IV develops the emergence of biological complexity from the same percolation threshold that governs QCD confinement and the actualization filter.
-
-The framework does not ask for acceptance. It asks for serious investigation.
+From a single ontological commitment---that irreversible actualization events write permanent vertices into a growing causal graph filtered by the BDG action---this paper establishes the kernel of Relational Actualism in native terms: seven axioms, a sequential growth rule, the BDG acceptance kernel, the local-ledger / graph-cut layer, the kernel-locality replacement family, and the arithmetic coefficient-inversion spine supporting the $d=4$ kernel.
+
+The strongest results of the present paper are therefore finitary and structural. The measurement problem is dissolved by making actualization primitive; sparse and dense regimes become two behaviours of the same event-writing process; finite propagation, event-count time, and saturation / partition structure follow directly from the graph-growth picture; and the case for $d=4$ is stated as a native multi-criterion programme anchored by a compiled arithmetic core.
+
+Historical AQFT, Lorentz, on-shell, coupling-constant, and other bridge cartographies have been removed from the active proof line of the paper. They may remain useful as downstream comparisons, but they are not what makes RA succeed or fail. Papers~II--IV extend the same kernel natively into matter / motif structure, severance / cosmology, and complexity / life. The framework does not ask to be translated first. It asks to be tested directly against Nature on its own terms.
 
